The paper deals with the problem of solving Hamiltonian Cycle on graphs of bounded clique width, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithm design. The techniques used in the paper involve representative sets and two-edge colored multigraphs, which are common tools in the study of graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
